com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.documents

Class DocumentNoteField

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.documents.DocumentNoteField

  • public final class DocumentNoteField
extends Object
    Describes the properties of a single value in a note. This does not contain the value itself. A note type (DocumentNoteType) consists of one or more of these fields.

    Constructed using the various create*NoteField factory methods in this class.

        public boolean isUserModificationAllowed()

      • isEnumeratedField

        public boolean isEnumeratedField()
        An enumerated field can only take a value from a predifined set of values (of String type). This is enforced by DocumentNote.setFieldValue(String, Object) such that a note may never have a value that is not in the enumeration values.
        Returns:
        true if this field is enumerated, false otherwise.
        See Also:
        getEnumerationValues()
